title: For Sale:  Century Arms VZ2008
postcontent:
For Sale:  Century Arms VZ2008
Century Arms VZ2008.  Excellent Condition.  Originally issued to the Czech army in 1958, the VZ58 is still in use by both the Czech and Slovak armies, their police and customs agents. Though similar to the other rifles of this style in appearance, the VZ58 uses a completely different bolt and fire control system. Even with a machined receiver, the VZ2008 is lighter than most similarly styled firearms with a sheet metal receiver. title: For Sale:  AK / AKM / AK47 Wood Furniture Set; Red; New
postcontent:
This auction is for one refinished, new AK furniture set. It was bought factory new and the original production brown finish was stripped, refinished a Russian red style color, then given several coatings of polyurethane for protection and for a glossy look. The set was USA manufactured and so it counts for several 922r compliance parts. It fits standard stamped AK’s and will not fit Yugos, Chinese rifles, VEPRs, milled receivers, or other non-standard rifles. See Timbersmith AK furniture sets for more details.
Due to the slight variance in dimensions between AK’s, the user will need to fit the wood set to their rifle. Generous amounts of polyurethane were applied to the areas where the wood mates with the rifle so the user can sand down those areas to ensure a snug fit. Also, the user will need to drill the two screw holes in the buttstock to attach it to the tang of the rifle. Drill bit, screws, and fitting instructions will be included along with a grip screw and T-nut. This kit does not come with an upper handguard retainer spring or a lower handguard U-shaped barrel support insert.
I am a college student who moved to the city and I no longer have time or money for shooting, but I refinish stock sets and other odds and ends to stay active in the hobby. Therefore, I do not claim to be a professional at finishing wood, but I take pride in my work and I am confident that you will be satisfied with this beautiful furniture set.
Thank you for taking time to view this auction and if you have any questions or concerns, please don’t hesitate to ask!
Note: Please be aware of your state’s laws regarding firearm related purchases.

title: For Sale:  Manurhin MR 73 4"
postcontent: Have for sale a Manurhin MR 73 4" French revolver. If you don't know what a MR 73 is, the French issue these beautifully hand-crafted works of art to their special weapons and tactical police teams (RAID,GIGN). They are absolutely built to last, requiring over 12 hours of hand fitting during manufacture. Likened to the Colt Python but built on a frame to withstand greater use. There are not many examples Stateside and they quickly sell when available. This particular example is a French police trade imported to the U.S. but in very good condition. It has obviously seen use and rounds down range during its time issued in France. I put a few boxes to verify function. The trigger return spring and hammer spring are both adjustable. A quick setting of the adjustable screws to increase tension on the trigger return spring and this revolver has proven reliable through a couple hundred rounds of .357 and .38 special. Bluing is beautiful, but does show wear from use. This is one of the better examples I've seen show up in these small imported batches. Barrel bore has mirror shine and is excellent. The revolver wears the Trausch rubber grips that absorb recoil quite well. Accuracy was excellent with quality loads as it should be. The MR 73s are held to the highest of standards during manufacture.  I'm moving this to fund some optics for different projects.  I actually had this listed on Gunbroker and had plenty of interest but pulled it due to a change of heart mid-way through the listing.  Well, I'm back to where I started and am deciding it's time to give to get.  $775 is the price.  I may eventually move this to auction.  FOID card and verification online is required for purchase.  Please feel free to ask questions.  Thank you.
